function [factor] = varcon(matrix,newvar)% function [factor] = varcon(matrix,newvar)% % calculates the constant needed to mutiply matrix% by to change its contrast variance to newvar. to% change the variance of matrix to newvar, mutliply% matrix by factor (the number returned by this function).% % July 21, 1998  JMG U of T Vision Labfactor = sqrt(newvar/std(matrix(:))^2);return